🟦 Permalist Project (To-Do List with Database)
🔹 1. Project Idea
Build a permanent to-do list
Uses PostgreSQL to store data
Data does not disappear after refresh or server restart
🔹 2. CRUD Operations

App supports:

Create → Add new task
Read → Display tasks
Update → Edit task
Delete → Remove task
🔹 3. Problem Before Database
Data stored in array (temporary)
Lost when server restarts ❌
🔹 4. Solution
Store data in database table: items
CREATE TABLE items(
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  title VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL
);
🔹 5. Backend Setup
Use:
Node.js
Express
pg package (connect to Postgres)
🔹 6. Read Data (Display)
SELECT * FROM items ORDER BY id ASC;
Fetch all tasks from database
🔹 7. Create (Add Task)
INSERT INTO items (title)
VALUES ('Buy milk');
🔹 8. Update (Edit Task)
UPDATE items
SET title = 'Buy bread'
WHERE id = 1;
🔹 9. Delete Task
DELETE FROM items
WHERE id = 1;
🔹 10. Key Concept
Data is now persistent (saved permanently)
Page refresh = data still exists ✅
🔹 11. Extra Features (Ideas)
Add date column (ALTER TABLE)
Multiple lists (daily, weekly)
User-based lists (relationships)
🧠 Final Summary

Build a to-do app using Postgres where all CRUD operations are stored permanently in a database instead of temporary memory.